\b\fs30 \cf0 Roomote Server Source Code\

\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\sa360\ql\qnatural
\ls5\ilvl0\cf0 The Roomote Server source code is available under the GNU General Public License.You are free to make modifications and redistribute the software under the terms of the GPL. You may download the code at {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.brianhpratt.net/roomote/"}}{\fldrslt http://www.brianhpratt.net/roomote/}}\
I especially encourage anyone to make a Windows version of this software. I'm sure that a totally Java version of the Roomote Server could be done that would be cross-platform. I initially created this project just to experiment with coding on the Mac OS X platform and don't have enough time or interest to rewrite the project for other platforms. I would be happy to help someone else's efforts, though. Feel free to contact me at {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://roomote@brianhpratt.net"}}{\fldrslt roomote@brianhpratt.net}}. I will happy link to your Windows/Linux port from this page as well.\
\ls5\ilvl0
\b\fs32 Included Code
\b0\fs24 \
The Roomote Server was created with the help of other open source projects, namely Tod E. Kurt's roombalib and the RoombaComm Java libraries. Both of these projects are available through {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://hackingroomba.com/"}}{\fldrslt http://hackingroomba.com/}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.dprg.org/projects/2009-07a/"}}{\fldrslt http://www.dprg.org/projects/2009-07a/}}.\
